Rating: 3
Tips: salt the potato water. Use uniform size potatoes so it's easier to know when they're cooked - and watch them closely. Tarragon is another idea. This is French-style potato salad and is meant to be simple. Definitely use sea salt and extra virgin olive oil. Let it sit awhile to develop flavors and serve room temperature. It's great on a hot day with grilled marinated meat.

Rating: 3
This recipe is definitely better with baby potatoes; I used small Yukon Gold potatoes, but they were still hard to gauge when the potatoes were cooked. I think I overcooked a few of them as they squished as I tried to cut them up. Otherwise, recipe made as is - very tasty! I agree with the reviewer who said to use a high quality extra-virgin olive oil for added flavor. Not sure what everyone's talking about re: a "lot of salt" needed. The amount of salt I added was several heavy-duty pinches, and that seemed to do the trick.

