Rating: 3
I think the key here is to add a vinagrette to the potatoes rather than just olive oil. we used about a pound of baby reds with a 1/4 cup of olive oil and 2 tablespoons of white wine vinegar(adding 1/2 teaspoon of salt and the shallots)which seemed to work pretty well. Overall, a pretty solid potatoe recipe that we would make again.

